      <td>Property</td>
      <td>Value</td>
      <td>How to obtain</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>Average storage\nconsumption</td>
      <td>GB consumed/day\nPercent consumed/day</td>
      <td>Go to the Grid Manager. On the Nodes page, select\nthe entire grid or a site and go to the Storage tab.\nOn the Storage Used - Object Data chart, find a\nperiod where the line is fairly stable. Position your\ncursor over the chart to estimate how much storage is\nconsumed each day\nYou can collect this information for the entire system\nor for a specific data center.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Average metadata\nconsumption</td>
      <td>GB consumed/day\nPercent consumed/day</td>
      <td>Go to the Grid Manager. On the Nodes page, select\nthe entire grid or a site and go to the Storage tab.\nOn the Storage Used - Object Metadata chart, find a\nperiod where the line is fairly stable. Position your\ncursor over the chart to estimate how much metadata\nstorage is consumed each day\nYou can collect this information for the entire system\nor for a specific data center.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Rate of S3/Swift\noperations</td>
      <td>Operations/second</td>
      <td>On the Grid Manager dashboard, select Performance\n&gt; S3 operations or Performance &gt; Swift\noperations.\nTo see ingest and retrieval rates and counts for a\nspecific site or node, select NODES &gt; site or Storage\nNode &gt; Objects. Position your cursor over the Ingest\nand Retrieve chart for S3 or Swift.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>Failed S3/Swift operations</td>
      <td>Operations</td>
      <td>Select SUPPORT &gt; Tools &gt; Grid topology. On the\nOverview tab in the API Operations section, view the\nvalue for S3 Operations - Failed or Swift Operations -\nFailed.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>ILM evaluation rate</td>
      <td>Objects/second</td>
      <td>From the Nodes page, select grid &gt; ILM.\nOn the ILM Queue chart, find a period where the line\nis fairly stable. Position your cursor over the chart to\nestimate a baseline value for Evaluation rate for your\nsystem.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
